Goldman Sachs faced criticism after setting aside nearly $17 billion (nearly $300 billion) for bonuses in the first three quarters of this year.
The total amount of bonuses in the entity for this year, according to Reuters, probably exceeds, despite the measure announced today, the $20 billion dollars.
High bonuses in the banking sector became, with the onset of the financial crisis, a sensitive issue in politics.
Britain announced on Wednesday that it plans to tax bank bonuses over 25,000 pounds (about CZK 712,000) at a one-time rate of fifty percent.
France is also preparing similar measures.
This year, women won the Nobel Prize in every category except physics.
Five women, a record number, received this year's Nobel Prizes in literature and specialised categories from King Charles XVI Gustav of Sweden in Stockholm today.
In addition to the four scientists, a German writer of Romanian origin, Herta Müller, was among the laureates.
The Nobel Prize in Medicine was awarded to two American biologists, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider, as well as their compatriot Jack Szostak for research in the field of chromosomes.
The Nobel Prize in Chemistry was awarded to Ada Jonath of Israel and Venkatraman Ramakrishna and Thomas Steitz of the United States for their explanation of the structure and function of ribosomes.
The last award, the Nobel Prize in Economics, went to the American Elinor Ostrom and her compatriot Oliver Williamson for the analysis of an economic report.
The only specialized category, without a female winner, was Physics.
This prize was awarded today to scientists Charles Kao for research in the field of optical cables, and George Smith and Willard Boyle for the invention of the CCD chip, which forms the basis of all digital cameras, fax machines and telescopes.
Each laureate received a diploma, a Nobel medal and a certificate of the money received.
This amount in each category is up to SEK 10 million (approximately SEK 25 million).
If there are several winners in each category, the prize is shared among them.
