This will provide you with a detailed itinerary of the next planned stage of the high-speed network.
The new line linking London to the West Midlands will be drawn within a five metre radius in urban areas and areas where environmental impact may be controversial.
In rural areas, the plan shall be drawn within a 25 m radius of a definitive route.
HS2 is also expected to set out three options for a wider high-speed network heading north.
Lord Adonis will answer in the spring.
The preferred option being proposed is a Y-shaped configuration, in which a single high-speed line would reach the West Midlands.
