Only one line would go into Scotland.
It seems this will be the most beneficial option", said a railway member.
Once completed, travel times between London and Edinburgh would be reduced to 2 hours and 40 minutes.
The first section, which would not open until 2025, would allow passengers to travel between London and Birmingham in 49 minutes, compared with just over an hour today.
The proposals would allow trains to travel at 402 km/h, making the British network the fastest in Europe.
